gating why a rocket engine exploded during testing]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>杰夫·贝佐斯的蓝色起源仍然遇到<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/blue-origin-pins-last-summers-ns-23-rocket-failure-on-a-faulty-engine-nozzle-195714293.html">技术问题</a>。该公司证实，6 月 30 日在德克萨斯州进行的点火测试中，一台 BE-4 发动机在大约 10 秒内发生爆炸。事件中没有人受伤，但<em>CNBC</em> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:CNBC;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34e37b9c-8975-48da-aa39-df8bcd5badc3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=CNBC&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXuuLNl0v_pnfJSJZHIg-UEJBlHNdcMTvdGJhy8L21Iz&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F07%2F11%2Fjeff-bezos-blue-origin-be-4-rocket-engine-explodes-during-testing.html" class="rapid-with-clickid">了解到</a>，该发动机本应被送往联合发射联盟 (ULA)，用于其第二次<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ula-may-4th-vulcan-centaur-rocket-inaugural-flight-125513492.html">火神</a>火箭飞行。</p><p>调查仍在进行中。蓝色起源表示，它已经找到了爆炸的“直接原因”，并且正在采取未具体说明的“补救措施”。一位发言人表示，该公司将继续测试火箭，并希望满足客户的发动机需求。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>这次爆炸是在新谢泼德火箭发生故障几个月后发生的，该故障最终归咎于发动机喷嘴损坏。 ULA 也有自己的麻烦。一枚火箭的上级在三月份发生爆炸，引发了调查并进行了修复，其中包括在该级上加厚钢墙。</p><p>无论这次挫折对蓝色起源的生产水平影响有多大，对于一家以发动机为业务重点的公司来说，这都不是好消息。 ULA 的每枚火神火箭都需要两台 BE-4 发动机，而蓝色起源即将推出的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nasa-blue-origin-new-glenn-escapade-science-mission-mars-110049165.html">New Glenn</a>则需要 7 台。这两辆车对于太空探索任务以及亚马逊的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-project-kuiper-launch-partners-131048042.html">柯伊伯项目</a>宽带卫星都至关重要。</p><p>蓝色起源的私人航天竞争对手也有自己的问题。 SpaceX <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spacexs-starship-completes-its-first-fully-integrated-flight-test-but-fails-to-reach-orbit-134226956.html">仍在努力</a>将 Starship 送入轨道，而维珍银河刚刚完成<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/virgin-galactic-completes-its-first-commercial-spaceflight-161701356.html">首次商业飞行</a>。那么，有缺陷的发动机不一定会成为主要障碍，即使它确实迫使公司调整时间表。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/blue-origin-is-investigating-why-a-rocket-engine-exploded-during-testing-210049055.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/blue-origin-is-investigating-why-a-rocket-engine-exploded-during-testing-210049055.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3cff39c3-f250-47e7-bb40-a15a337b1bd3</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 11 Jul 2023 21:00:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689108959</ingested><modified> 2023-07-11T20:56:03+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3fcb3a70-202b-11ee-ad7e-b5c0179a433d" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3fcb3a70-202b-11ee-ad7e-b5c0179a433d" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Blue Origin]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Blue Origin BE-4 engine firing test]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Blue Origin BE-4 engine firing test]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Amazon Prime Day TV deals for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-prime-day/">亚马逊 Prime Day</a>已经开始，并带来了许多电视折扣。如果您一直在寻找新的电视机，我们在下面汇总了我们可以找到的最佳黄金日电视优惠。虽然我们不会在 Engadget 上正式评测电视，但我们仔细研究了用户和我们信任的其他网站的评论，以确保您不会浪费金钱。电视市场目前正处于过渡期，因此请注意，我们选择的许多型号都是 2022 年的型号，它们与其后继产品足够接近，但价格却低得多。如果您不需要新电视，我们还为媒体流媒体提供了一些 Prime Day 优惠。</p><h2>三星S95B </h2><p><core-commerce id="8419a84dd42b433595b2dcf964be6336" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> 65 英寸<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZTJRkGCl3I0zdzfjmtX1Muq5sUJRTJcofqq1pnkELnY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09VHBLV4Y%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09VHBLV4Y/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;psc=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">三星 S95B</a>售价为 1,598 美元，创下历史最低价。通常情况下，这套高评价的套装近几个月要额外花费 100 至 200 美元。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> S95B 的 QD-OLED 面板将 OLED 技术与量子点层相结合，使其能够提供高对比度和宽视角，而不会在亮度和色彩饱和度方面牺牲典型 OLED 电视的性能。这意味着即使在更明亮的房间里它也应该提供丰富的图像。 It can also play up to 4K 120Hz, which is handy for the PS5 or Xbox Series X, but like all Samsung TVs, it doesn&#39;t support Dolby Vision HDR.</p><p> The S95B is a 2022 model, so it&#39;s on the way out in favor of the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJXRlNGRDdQP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAecfQEa29xZLo30hKbSNR3xgCuDsauYe9icE7Z6yxstG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BWFSFD7P" class="rapid-with-clickid">new S95C</a> . The latter supports a faster 144Hz refresh rate and runs its ports through an external box, which makes the design thinner. Other <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/reviews/samsung/s95c-oled">reviewers</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/features/samsung-s95b-vs-samsung-s95c-which-should-you-buy">say</a> it can get a bit brighter, too. But the S95 currently costs <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJXRlNGRDdQP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAecfQEa29xZLo30hKbSNR3xgCuDsauYe9icE7Z6yxstG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BWFSFD7P" class="rapid-with-clickid">$2,298</a> and <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJXRlQyNjJQP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAYW3kaXb_SVCRKhies2qJqwCF3DnHfGT0HkhsIk3HbnO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BWFT262P" class="rapid-with-clickid">$2,998</a> for a 55- and 65-inch model, respectively, and its upgrades don&#39;t appear to be massive enough to justify that extra cost for most. If you&#39;re in the market for a premium TV, the S95B should remain the better value while it&#39;s still available.</p><h2> LG C2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="77e7af04a0964c1790294ea37b0abb82" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> For a (relatively) more affordable OLED TV, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlSTUxMSlBYP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAaNqXKfs-hTJzTEevQNkeUwYbYKKDFpYJKrW-h1mSaGT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09RMLLJPX" class="rapid-with-clickid">LG C2</a> is down to $1,097 for a 55-inch model, $1,496 for a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARf2icum9QS3U4AnvyKAAZbPXx6rWhgZGCHFFQmyjdrn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09RMRNSBF%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09RMRNSBF/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;psc=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">65-inch model</a> and $797 for a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlSTUZaWlBYP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAV-E5fnuQeJGD-wHzQgYwFv1G9S6I-eLQpA7pgbbhmZS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09RMFZZPX" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09RMFZZPX?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">42-inch model</a> . None of these are all-time lows, but they&#39;re each about $140 below their respective street prices. The C2 can&#39;t match the brightness and color range of a QD-OLED set like the Samsung S95B, but it still offers excellent contrast, deep black levels and wide viewing angles. It has four HDMI 2.1 ports that can play 4K at 120Hz, it supports <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-tvs-for-gaming-180033983.html">gaming-friendly features</a> like <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/variablerefreshrate">VRR</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/autolowlatencymode">ALLM</a> , and it comes in a wider range of sizes than the S95B. It works with all the major HDR formats, too, Dolby Vision included. It&#39;s just less ideal in a brightly-lit room.</p><p> LG has rolled out a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJWWEY3MkhWLz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby0xOGEtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIzNzhjYzIyLTIxOGQtNDZiMC1iMDkxLTgwOWQ5ZDg2NDc2ZiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQ1-utsrmfGz8DzugBTdMXMDjKTF_k6B3Q2hru6vc2Vq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BVXF72HV%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">new C3 model</a> for 2023, but it&#39;s pricier, and <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.cnet.com/tech/home-entertainment/lg-oled-c3-review-sets-the-standard-for-high-end-television-picture-quality/">many</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/features/lg-c3-vs-lg-c2">reviews</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/tools/compare/lg-c2-oled-vs-lg-c3-oled/31229/37848?usage=1&amp;threshold=0.10">suggest</a> it&#39;s only a marginal upgrade outside of adding support for DTS audio.</p><h2> Sony A80K </h2><p><core-commerce id="7b54f7cc0bdb4e428946860051e88366" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If the LG C2 goes out of stock, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlSOTNUV1RRP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAUqWxdV4Pxgt0ttR0LKq3v6frPIXjO-0FbFHlD5dpQM6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09R93TWTQ" class="rapid-with-clickid">Sony A80K</a> is another commendable OLED TV. It&#39;s down to $1,098 for a 55-inch model and $1,498 for a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlSOUpQU1RIP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAT9KF3bTwtJzD66M8nqofeciUsJP-RIB3kIHG8RJ8ku6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09R9JPSTH" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09R9JPSTH?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">65-inch model</a> . Both deals mark new lows: The former is about $250 off its recent street price, while the latter is a roughly $300 discount. The C2 is broadly considered a better option thanks to its <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/tools/compare/sony-a80k-oled-vs-lg-c2-oled/31219/31229?usage=1&amp;threshold=0.10">superior brightness</a> levels and two extra HDMI 2.1 ports, but the A80K still gets you the core benefits of an OLED display. It also runs on Google TV, which some may prefer to LG&#39;s webOS platform. Like the C2, you&#39;ll get the most out of it if you stay away from glare.</p><p> Sony&#39;s 2023 follow-up, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQ744hs0zUtdrLeGbAd2hpqEBUkKY1dqum-EeNwXbhy5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-OLED-inch-BRAVIA-Ultra%2Fdp%2FB0BYPVKW72" class="rapid-with-clickid">the A80L</a> , should be a better buy when prices come down, but right now it starts at $1,698. At that price, most should be better off with the Samsung S95B.</p><h2> LG B2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="0f41232957e14500af55d3fe3c17416a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you want a decent OLED TV for as little as possible, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATvpPBwnm1qG7Gs-jZVX_yPuX9AQrY9JkXpUrdHX8iSJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLG-55-Inch-Refresh-AI-Powered-OLED55B2PUA%2Fdp%2FB09RMND29B" class="rapid-with-clickid">55-inch LG B2</a> is a solid value at $897, which is a new low and a little over $100 off its typical street price. Again, this TV isn&#39;t as bright or color-rich as the C2 with HDR content, and it&#39;s limited to two HDMI 2.1 ports. It also runs on a slower processor. Still, the contrast and motion performance here will be a noticeable upgrade if you&#39;re coming from a more basic LCD TV and want to stay under $1,000. The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAf6ev85_QKZnS483av-pt6wat20wilm4grwbONP0aBRA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLG-55-Inch-Refresh-AI-Powered-OLED55B2PUA%2Fdp%2FB09RMR23XL" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/LG-55-Inch-Refresh-AI-Powered-OLED55B2PUA/dp/B09RMR23XL?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">65-inch model</a> is also on sale for $1,197.</p><p> We&#39;ll also note the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Best Buy;elmt:;cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5e0bed65-d2f8-4b34-9b8f-955218c0e37a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Best+Buy&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdh4gZPfCo-nASCJPktalB8XrZsXtpQYGQjJyNgS7kvf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Flg-48-class-a2-series-oled-4k-uhd-smart-webos-tv%2F6501902.p" class="rapid-with-clickid">LG A2</a> , which is down to $600 for a 48-inch model at Best Buy. That&#39;s a nice price if you really want an OLED display, though it&#39;s a further step down in brightness, it&#39;s limited to a 60Hz refresh rate and it lacks HDMI 2.1 features for gaming.</p><h2> Samsung QN90B </h2><p><core-commerce id="eb48a08959444a38ad46c067ae35c079" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAftn9YvZ7t3u457XuSWxABcu6Eip-fc65lJYTQox-rc9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09SBHSNNZ%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09SBHSNNZ/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;psc=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Samsung QN90B</a> is back down to $1,098 for a 55-inch model. That&#39;s not the best price we&#39;ve seen, but it&#39;s still about $100 off its usual street price. If you&#39;re looking for a smaller set, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlXRzcyNjJYP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAb6Yfkop8PDFAV5i692HfHm8R4KjAnmoh_oz-PaDSufe&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09WG7262X" class="rapid-with-clickid">43-inch version</a> <em>is</em> at an all-time low of $898. The QN90B is an LCD TV, so it can&#39;t supply the near-perfect blacks and super wide viewing angles of an OLED panel, but it can get significantly brighter, and <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.cnet.com/tech/home-entertainment/samsung-qn90b-review-this-qled-tv-from-the-futures-so-bright/">reviews</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-lcd-led-tv/">say</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1" href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/content/samsung-qn90b-neo-qled-tv-review">it</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/reviews/samsung/qn90b-qled">provides</a> better contrast than most non-OLED TVs thanks to its Mini LED backlight. There&#39;s still no Dolby Vision, but it gives you four full HDMI 2.1 ports, 4K/120Hz support and multiple types of VRR. If you want a high-end TV for a room plagued by glare, it&#39;s a good buy.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:31;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJUVFZMNDE5P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAASnQbgq-tw_G7_yREolLDaK9JOMk3zko5qsDu-k2qXqO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BTTVL419" class="rapid-with-clickid">new QN90C</a> is out but costs much more, so again, last year&#39;s set is still the better buy for now. If you opt for the 43-inch model, note that it has worse viewing angles than the larger variants but also supports a faster 144Hz refresh rate. That feature should be useful if you want a TV that can double as a gaming PC monitor.</p><h2> Samsung The Frame TV </h2><p><core-commerce id="216e2497634b4550ae31ed60a9c28e46" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Samsung&#39;s 55-inch <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:32;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlWQ1ZHSDdCP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAZvofY705Rsi482DL31XUn3XEhmA_N_09j28o6SHUG5C&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09VCVGH7B" class="rapid-with-clickid">The Frame TV</a> is down to $988, which is a new low and about $450 off its typical street price. The Frame is a TV for those willing to trade some picture quality for classy aesthetics, as it&#39;s designed to look like a piece of art you can mount against a wall. When you aren&#39;t watching something, you can use it to display artwork and photos. A few pieces come included, while others are sold with a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:33;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAW6bIUqHB2ldP4IjbBhBlxE7I2w88jfukKvngbg58cAy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftelevisions-home-theater%2Ftvs%2Fthe-frame%2Fdigital-art-store%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">subscription</a> . The Frame&#39;s QLED panel lacks local dimming, so its contrast and HDR performance can&#39;t really compete with the best options in its price range. It only has one HDMI 2.1 port, too. But the image is still far from poor, and its design does well to blend into a wall, as <a data-i13n="cpos:34;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-the-frame-tv-irl-153546368.html">we&#39;ve professed before</a> .</p><h2> Hisense A6H </h2><p