;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9IaXNlbnNlLTU1LUluY2gtVmlydHVhbC1DaHJvbWVjYXN0LTU1QTZIL2RwL0IwOVdRTllaR1Y_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMThhLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMzc4Y2MyMi0yMThkLTQ2YjAtYjA5MS04MDlkOWQ4NjQ3NmYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAARI9tTE-h9ajtQXEmOGYjb4jN_zSrPtm3-2YuQ1dTcoE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHisense-55-Inch-Virtual-Chromecast-55A6H%2Fdp%2FB09WQNYZGV" class="rapid-with-clickid">43-inch set</a> . Both deals match all-time lows. The A6H is very much an entry-level 4K TV, so don&#39;t expect especially high contrast or rich colors compared to pricier options. There&#39;s no local dimming, and it&#39;s limited to a 60Hz refresh rate. But for this price, its picture is perfectly fine. The 50-inch model&#39;s VA panel should be particularly decent in a dark room, though it&#39;ll have narrower viewing angles than the 43-inch set&#39;s IPS display. And while it can be sluggish to navigate apps, its Google TV interface makes it easy to find things to watch. None of this will blow you away, but as a cheap secondary TV, the A6H should do the job.</p><p> If you&#39;re looking for a more mid-range option, consider the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:38;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAT9Oco3kipk3b11Iiis2JpujOXrwE1jNLjxFFYnBMiIB&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHisense-Class-Mini-LED-Google-75U6K%2Fdp%2FB0C6WLWQ5R%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Hisense U6K</a> . It costs $500 for a 55-inch model and offers Mini LED backlighting, which is rare for the cost. <a data-i13n="cpos:39;pos:1" href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/content/hisense-u6k-mini-led-tv-review">Recent</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:40;pos:1" href="https://www.pcmag.com/reviews/hisense-65-inch-u6-series-uled-tv-65u6k">reviews</a> say it delivers better contrast control and color volume than most TVs in its price range as a result, though it&#39;s still limited to 60Hz and doesn&#39;t have the widest viewing angles. It&#39;s not priced any lower than usual for Prime Day, either.</p><h2> Amazon Fire TV Omni QLED Series </h2><p><core-commerce id="b1d4fb74b1d34320b792cc7c5484e7fc" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:41;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAW4JQv3J9Geh452rjEHC546uryriUWUxBnfC2LAog-39&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09N6LRBTR%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09N6LRBTR/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;psc=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Amazon&#39;s Fire TV Omni QLED Series</a> is on sale in several sizes for Prime Day, with the 43-, 50-, 55- and 65-inch models down to <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:42;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlONkxSQlRSP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAcxC8fXTtqLzyg7rnQQKbJliel9IO8rmANBsdK3e8hRG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09N6LRBTR" class="rapid-with-clickid">$380</a> , <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:43;pos: